The President commends Congress for passing the Medicare Access and CHIP Reauthorization Act, which ends the annual uncertainty faced by physicians regarding their Medicare payments. The bill also strengthens the healthcare system by rewarding providers for better-quality care and incentivizing participation in innovative payment models. Additionally, it extends the Children's Health Insurance Program. The President plans to sign the bipartisan bill into law and encourages Congress to continue working towards ensuring that all Americans have access to quality, affordable healthcare.